post_text:
Great things come from Argos! 💪🏻

#WeLoveOurDragons #WhereKidsComeFirst
shared_text:
Marshall County Museum Historic Crossroads Center
September 6 at 10:00 AM ·

The iconic Blueberry Hank was the product of a drawing contest in the 1970s. The Marshall County Blueberry Festival Board was looking for ideas for a mascot and Ed Miller’s submission was the winner. Ed Miller was an art teacher at Argos Community Schools for 38 years. His original design was donated to the Museum, and is pictured below, to commemorate the creation of one of the most recognizable “people” in Marshall County. Through all the years of the festival, Blueberry Hank remains a timeless representative of all the memories, good times (& food!) and sense community the festival has brought.

This is for any fans next week that might be heading to a game vs. LaVille
*No tickets for LV events will be sold at the gate. All tickets must be purchased ahead of time on lavilleathletics.com. Please let your fan base know this, and tickets are $5 for High school and $4 for Jr. High. There is also a $1.49 fee for every ticket sold. If an event is cancelled, fans will be refunded the face value cost of the ticket, but not the processing fees.

post_text:
Summer meal service resumes on June 1 for all that have previously requested this service for June 1 - June 30. Meals will be delivered Monday - Thursday with 2 meals for each child being delivered on Thursdays. This meals service will continue to be available for bus drop off or for pick up. If you will no longer need meal service in June or need to make any changes to your request, please call the Administration office at 574-892-5139 or send an email to questions@argos.k12.in.us
If you have not signed up for meal service and need lunch delivery to your home, please complete the form found under our COVID-19 banner at www.argos.k12.in.us Lunches will be delivered by our transportation team and will be brought to your door. Delivery will begin at 11:00 a.m. There are new family additions to our deliveries daily so your family should always be watching for our delivery team and be ready to receive the meals you have requested.

post_text: Last night we held our annual Scholarship and awards night for our seniors, via Zoom. While it is not how we wanted to host this event, we are making the best of a bad situation. post_text:
Argos Junior-Senior High School is proud to announce the top scholars for the Class of 2020.

This year, the valedictorian for the Class of 2020 is Andrew Harley. Andrew is the son of Shawn and Michele Harley of Argos. Over the past four years, Andrew has been very active in the Argos chapter of FFA in both leadership and in volunteer work. Andrew is also a member of the National Honor Society.
Andrew plans to attend Indiana Institute of Technology in Fort Wayne, where he will study software engineering.

Achieving the honor of salutatorian is Evan Cohagan. Evan is the son of Myron and Elizabeth Cohagan of Rochester. Throughout high school, Evan has been involved in many activities, including band and show choir, bowling team, Quiz Bowl, and National Honor Society. He is a 10-year member of 4-H and has been an integral part of Argos FFA, serving as chapter president this year.
Evan will be heading to West Lafayette in the fall to attend Purdue University and major in biochemistry, biophysics, and molecular biology.

Over the past four years, Andrew has been very active in the Argos chapter of FFA in both leadership and in volunteer work. Andrew is also a member of the National Honor Society.
Andrew plans to attend Indiana Institute of Technology in Fort Wayne, where he will study software engineering.

Achieving the honor of salutatorian is Evan Cohagan. Evan is the son of Myron and Elizabeth Cohagan of Rochester. Throughout high school, Evan has been involved in many activities, including band and show choir, bowling team, Quiz Bowl, and National Honor Society. He is a 10-year member of 4-H and has been an integral part of Argos FFA, serving as chapter president this year.
Evan will be heading to West Lafayette in the fall to attend Purdue University and major in biochemistry, biophysics, and molecular biology.

Argos Community Schools is providing free lunches for children during the Emergency Closure days until May 22, 2020. Lunches may be picked up at the Jr.-Sr. High entrance between 11:00 a.m. - 12:15 p.m.

Summer meal service resumes for all that have previously requested this service for June 1 - June 30. This will continue to be available for bus drop off or for pick up. If you will no longer need meal service in June or need to make any changes to your request, please call the Administration office at 574-892-5139 or send an email to questions@argos.k12.in.us

For lunch delivery to your home please complete the form found under our COVID-19 banner at www.argos.k12.in.us Lunches will be delivered by our transportation team and will be brought to your door. Delivery will begin at 11:00 a.m. There are new family additions to our deliveries daily so your family should always be watching for our delivery team and be ready to receive the meals you have requested. We are not able to give you an exact time your lunches will be delivered each day.

post_text:
As the COVID 19 situation continues to unfold in our communities, the Bowen Center is keenly aware that the need for existing and new counseling is a continued need. Argos Community Schools provides a current Student Assistance Program (SAP) that offers our students free/prepaid counseling sessions. This SAP benefit is still available by phone with the Bowen Center. To set up a counseling appointment, please call 1 (800) 342-5653. More information about our Student Assistance Program can also be viewed at this link. https://www.bowencenter.org/student-assistance

The Bowen Center is also aware that how to talk with children during infectious disease outbreaks is very important these days. For tips to caregivers, parents and teachers, these are some very helpful tips on how to navigate those types of discussions as listed on the SAMSHA website at https://store.samhsa.gov/product/Talking-With-Children-Tips-for-Caregivers-Parents-and-Teachers-During-Infectious-Disease-Outbreaks/PEP20-01-01-006?referer=from_search_result

post_text: Please plan to attend Hacienda Plymouth on Wednesday, January 29 for lunch OR dinner! 20% of your purchase will go towards Argos BPA to help with the cost of competitions. And finally, if you would like to help support Argos BPA but can't help on that particular day, please consider buying a gift card which will also count towards the 20% they receive. Please see a BPA member or Shari Bloom for a coupon or to order a gift card! (Note: A paper copy of the coupon must be presented--Not a picture of one) Thanks!

UPDATE: All of our families have been adopted!! Thank you so much for your generosity!

Are you looking for a way to give back this Christmas?
We have 3 families waiting to be adopted from our STAR Tree. We suggest that $50 be spent per child to insure that each child can receive a few things that they need as well as a wish item. Gifts are due back to the elementary on December 13th. This is a great opportunity for a group to work together to help a family in need this Christmas! text:
UPDATE: All of our families have been adopted!! Thank you so much for your generosity!

Are you looking for a way to give back this Christmas?
We have 3 families waiting to be adopted from our STAR Tree. We suggest that $50 be spent per child to insure that each child can receive a few things that they need as well as a wish item. Gifts are due back to the elementary on December 13th. This is a great opportunity for a group to work together to help a family in need this Christmas! Please contact the elementary office at 574-892-5139 for more information or to adopt a family.

The Argos Dragonflies Entomology Teams dominated the 4-H/FFA Area X Entomology Judging Contest held at the Kosciusko County Fairgrounds recently.

Argos took two junior teams and one senior individual to the contest. The Argos Dragonflies Gold team placed first and the Argos Dragonflies Black team placed second. This makes both junior teams eligible to participate in the State Entomology Contest to be held at Purdue University on December 14.

Pictured back row, left to right: Makenzie Smith, Argos Dragonflies Gold; Lilly Pask, Senior Dragonfly; Marisa Kline, Argos Dragonflies Black.

Center row, left to right: Tristan Hutchison, Argos Dragonflies Gold; June Clark, Argos Dragonflies Gold.

Front row, left to right: Trinity Hensley, Argos Dragonflies Black, Kyndra Thayer, Argos Dragonflies Gold; Xander Binfet, Argos Dragonflies Black.
